From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: smolvm <smolvm@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 2 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 23/23] ovl: translate EOPNOTSUPP to ENOTTY in
 ovl_real_fileattr_get

FUSE servers (including virtiofs) that do not implement
FS_IOC_GETFLAGS / FS_IOC_FSGETXATTR return -EOPNOTSUPP from their
ioctl handler.  vfs_fileattr_get() propagates this unchanged, but
ovl_real_fileattr_get() only translates -ENOIOCTLCMD to -ENOTTY.
The callers in copy_up.c treat -ENOTTY as "no fileattr support" and
continue, while -EOPNOTSUPP falls through to pr_warn + error return,
which makes every overlayfs copy-up over a virtiofs lower layer fail.

Translate -EOPNOTSUPP alongside -ENOIOCTLCMD in the single
chokepoint (ovl_real_fileattr_get) so all callers benefit.

Fixes: 72db82115d2b ("ovl: copy up sync/noatime fileattr flags")
Signed-off-by: smolvm <smolvm@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 fs/overlayfs/inode.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/fs/overlayfs/inode.c b/fs/overlayfs/inode.c
index 4e2cfb05b767..5e1867a0c213 100644
--- a/fs/overlayfs/inode.c
+++ b/fs/overlayfs/inode.c
@@ -721,7 +721,7 @@ int ovl_real_fileattr_get(const struct path *realpath, struct fileattr *fa)
 		return err;

 	err = vfs_fileattr_get(realpath->dentry, fa);
-	if (err == -ENOIOCTLCMD)
+	if (err == -ENOIOCTLCMD || err == -EOPNOTSUPP)
 		err = -ENOTTY;
 	return err;
 }
